<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3825196>
    dc:description "FIGURE 26. Lycopodina calyx (Hentschel, 1914). A. SEM of the sponge body QM G337513 B. Palmate anisochelae. C. Mycalostyle 1. D. Magnified ends of the mycalostyle 1 illustrated in C. E. Mycalostyle 2. F. Magnified ends of the mycalostyle 2 illustrated in E. G. Mycalostyle 3. H. Magnified ends of the mycalostyle 3 illustrated in G. I. SEM of the exterior of the sponge body (calyx), showing the large mycalostyles underneath the protecting medium mycalostyles. J. SEM of the inside of the cup. K. Preserved specimen QM G337463. L. Preserved specimen QM G337513. M. Preserved specimen QM G337476." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3825196/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3825148>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Abyssocladia annae sp. nov. A. Abyssochelae. B. Subtylostyle. C. Magnified ends of the subtylostyle depicted in B. D. Sigmancistra. E. Holotype QM G337611. F. SEM showing the abundant abyssochelae and sigmancistras in the ectosome and the underlying subtylostyles in the endosome." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3825148/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3825162>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. A. Type of Axoniderma mirabile, BMNH 1887.5.2.141. B. Pseudoamphiaster and an unguiferate anisochelae. C. Pseudoamphiaster. D. Pseudoamphiaster and an unguiferate anisochelae. E. Sigma. F. Section through a filament showing the encrusting pseudoamphiasters in the ectosome and two sizes of styles in the endosome. G. Section through the end of the filament showing the external layer of pseudoamphiasters and the anisochelae in the endosome. H. Section through the body of the sponge showing the intersection of the stem and the filament rays, with encrusting pseudoamphiasters. I Section through the body with ectosome of pseudoamphiasters and anisochelae in the endosome." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3825162/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3825146>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Maximum-likelihood phylogram of the DNA sequences of this study in comparison with other, published cornivorous sponges. Sequences from taxa of this study are in bold. Number at the branches are RAxML rapid bootstrap values. Numbers following the taxa are either QM registration numbers (QM G3xxxxx) or NCBI Genbank accession numbers. Scale bare are substitutions per site. Please note that the reconstruction does not represent a phylogeny as due to the variability of the 28SrRNA gene C-Region barcoding marker no unambiguous alignment is possible and clipping ambiguous sites would remove diagnostic characters for taxon distinction. The tree therefore indicates molecular differences rather than a robust phylogeny." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3825146/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3825166>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Cladorhiza investigator sp. nov. Holotype QM G337458. A. External view of the filaments showing the tightly packed anisochelae in the ectosome. B. The ectosome of the filaments exposed revealing the mycalostyles in the endosome. C. The external surface of the stem showing the ectosomal plates formed by the mycalostyles and the almost alternate juxtaposition of the filaments. D. Internal T.S. of the stem showing the mycalostyles buttressing the filaments after they have emerged from the confused core. In addition it shows the longitudinal tracks of mycalostyles. E. Cross section of the stem, showing the nine radial filaments intersecting in the core of the stem, and the thin wedges of anisochelae and sigmas between these arms. F. Branching roots of the sponge, showing an almost absent ectosome, but the tight bundles of mycalostyles and three thin subtylostyles in the upper branch." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3825166/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

